<scriptment id="61000" point="syringe" localizationstatus="original" fictionaldate="2011-09-04" status="final">
	<part>
		<narration>Yuki, flips through a multitude of channels.<comment>Player is in charge of the switch.</comment></narration>
		<line id="1000" speaker="tv" voicelang="en">Aren't you too old for video games &#x2014;</line>
		<line id="2000" speaker="tv" voicelang="en">&#x2014; Social deviants play video games &#x2014;</line>
		<line id="3000" speaker="tv" voicelang="ja">Virginia Tech &#x2014; Akihabara &#x2014; Columbine &#x2014; all gamers &#x2014;</line>
		<narration>Yuki shuts down the television.</narration>
		<line id="4000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">The advantage of passive media is its greater potential to herd sheep.</line>
		<line id="5000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">The syringe-media perception that those who work and play with video games are "bad people,"</line>
		<line id="6000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">messes everything up for the good ones.</line>
		<line id="7000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">Go ahead. Keep calling us the demons.</line>
		<line id="8000" speaker="yuki" voicelang="fr">And we will all become zombies.</line>
	</part>
</scriptment>